2.4.2.2. Shannon–Rényi entropies. Spontaneous breaking of a continuous symmetry also appears in the (basis-dependent)

so-called ‘‘Shannon–Rényi’’ (SR) entropy computed in the ground-state of finite size systems. These wave-function entropies,

recently introduced in series of works by Stéphan and co-workers [143,146,189], and further studied by other groups

[190–198], can efficiently capture universal properties, e.g. Luttinger liquid physics, quantum criticality, symmetry breaking

phases.

