2.5.2.2. Fractional quantum Hall states. The topological entanglement entropy has also been measured with a great accuracy
for Laughlin wave function at ν = 1/m [220,223,236,237] as well as for the non-abelian Moore–Read state [238,239]. In
Fig. 16 we report numerical results from Refs. [223,237,238]. More recently, non-abelian states such as fractional quantum

