.

(3.2)

This critical regime is described by a CFT [270] with central charge c = 1, yielding the logarithmic growth [21] of the

Rény entanglement entropies Eq. (2.3). Making a real-space bipartition, which defines a subsystem A (depicted in the

inset of Fig. 17), its RDM ρA has eigenvalues λi which gives the ES ξi = − ln λi. The eigenvalues distribution was first studied by Calabrese and Lefèvre [268] using CFT and exact diagonalization of Eq. (3.1) at ∆ = 0. Exploiting the fact that

