temperature

which

is

vanishing

with

the

subsystem size ∼(ln ℓ)/ℓ [54,275]. For Heisenberg chains T /J1

=

1 2

ln(ℓ/a)/ℓ,

thus

yielding

the

Calabrese–Cardy

