3.3.3.2. Néel ordered regime. Keeping the same one-dimensional setup for subsystem A, one can cross the critical point and
explore the Néel ordered side for g > gc , as done in Refs. [194,195]. In this regime, while the power-law model Eq. (3.19) gives reasonable KL (Fig. 33 top) for parameters (α − βeff) where finite temperature order is expected, a better agreement
