in Ref. [398] where typical and average have qualitatively different scalings.

The distribution of Tr ρA2, shown in the main panel of Fig. 35 for the random singlet state of random XX chains (exact diagonalization results) for increasing system lengths L = 16, . . . , 512, displays broadening at small values with increasing size, suggesting non-self-averaging entanglement.10 In the inset of Fig. 35, the log scalings are plotted for q = 1, 2, showing

a very good agreement with the analytical prediction Eqs. (4.1) and (4.2).

4.1.1.2. Random spin chains with higher spin. Infinite randomness fixed points also occur for s > 1/2 chains [417–420],
where Refael and Moore have shown [421] that

⟨SvN⟩

