exhibits a much slower logarithmic growth [585]. 19 And no random field, thus preserving the particle–hole symmetry of the Hamiltonian for which we do not expect Anderson localization. 20 This does not mean an equilibrated thermal state though. 21 This is relevant for dipolar cold gases, good candidates for observing MBL [597–599].

