This model displays two gapped rung-singlet phases if the inter-ladder coupling λ1c > λ > λ2c with λ1c = 0.31407(5) [381] and λ2c = 1.9096(2) [384], and a gapless Néel ordered phase in between, as shown in Fig. 53(a). T = 0 fluctuations of the total magnetization in a sub-system A of size L/2 × L, embedded in a periodic square lattice L × L are shown in Fig. 53 (b-c), with square lattices size up to L × L = 104, for the isotropic square lattice λ = 1 (Néel) and for weakly coupled ladders with λ = 0.1 (gapped rung singlet I). In contrast with the entanglement (or Rényi) entropy which displays a strict area law both
phases, the second cumulant follows different scalings [94]:

F

(ℓ)

∼

αℓ ln ℓ + β′ℓ + γ ′

